{{Lunisolar September}} 
'''September 28''' is the 28th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|12=draft|12=draft}} , the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft}}  and its day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=draft|12=draft}} .

== Events ==
* {{ill|Gentoku|ja|元徳|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year /{{ill|Genkō|ja|元弘|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|1331|ja|1331|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The exiled Emperor {{ill|Godaigo|ja|後醍醐天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}  took refuge in Kasagiyama; the Kamakura shogunate then turned against {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|Ashikaga Takauji|12=draft|12=draft}} , and the emperor was captured the following day.
* {{ill|Chōroku|ja|長禄|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|1457|ja|1457|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kōsei|ja|康正|12=draft|12=draft}}  to {{ill|Chōroku|ja|長禄|12=draft|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|1629|ja|1629|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|November 13|ja|11月13日|12=draft|12=draft}} ） – {{ill|Tokugawa Iefusa|ja|徳川頼房|12=draft|12=draft}}  completed the construction of a garden (later known as {{ill|Kōrakuen|ja|後楽園|12=draft|12=draft}} ) at his Mito domain villa in Koishikawa.
