'''September 28''' is the 28th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  and its day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} .

== Events ==
* {{ill|Gentoku|ja|元徳|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 3rd year /{{ill|Genkō|ja|元弘|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  {{ill|1331|ja|1331|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  {{ill|October 30|ja|10月30日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ） – The exiled Emperor {{ill|Godaigo|ja|後醍醐天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  took refuge in Kasagiyama; the Kamakura shogunate then turned against {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|Ashikaga Takauji|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , and the emperor was captured the following day.
* {{ill|Chōroku|ja|長禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 1st year（{{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  {{ill|1457|ja|1457|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  {{ill|October 16|ja|10月16日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ） – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kōsei|ja|康正|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  to {{ill|Chōroku|ja|長禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} .
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|寛永|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 6th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  {{ill|1629|ja|1629|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  {{ill|November 13|ja|11月13日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ） – {{ill|Tokugawa Iefusa|ja|徳川頼房|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}  completed the construction of a garden (later known as {{ill|Kōrakuen|ja|後楽園|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ) at his Mito domain villa in Koishikawa.
== Births ==
