{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q840059]] Wikidata name: 28th day of the 9th month in the Chinese calendar [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:14, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Not to be confused with|September 28|qq=September 28}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:17, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月廿八|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 28일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 28''' is the 28th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} , the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} and its day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=|1=Shakkō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11635368}} .
== Events == * [[:en:Gentoku|Gentoku]] 3rd year /[[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1331|1331]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]] ） – The exiled Emperor [[:en:Emperor Go-Daigo|Godaigo]] took refuge in Kasagiyama; the Kamakura shogunate then turned against {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|Ashikaga Takauji|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Takauji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} , and the emperor was captured the following day. * [[:en:Chōroku|Chōroku]] 1st year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1457|1457]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]] ） – The era name was changed from [[:en:Kōshō|Kōsei]] to [[:en:Chōroku|Chōroku]] . * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 6th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1629|1629]] [[:en:November 13|November 13]] ） – [[:en:Tokugawa Yorifusa|Tokugawa Iefusa]] completed the construction of a garden (later known as [[:en:Kōraku-en|Kōrakuen]] ) at his Mito domain villa in Koishikawa. == Births == * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 7th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1757|1757]] [[:en:November 9|November 9]] ） – {{ill|Ōtsuki Genzawa|ja|大槻玄沢|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtsuki Genzawa|qq=|1=Ōtsuki Gentaku|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q6531075}} , a rangaku scholar († [[:en:1827|1827]] ). * [[:en:Bunka|Bunka]] 6th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1809|1809]] [[:en:November 5|November 5]] ） – [[:en:Shimazu Nariakira|Shimazu Nariakira]] , lord of the Satsuma Domain († [[:en:1858|1858]] ). * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] [[:en:October 28|October 28]] ） – {{ill|Yokogawa Minosuke|ja|横河民輔|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokogawa Minosuke|qq=|1=Tamisuke Yokogawa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11542812}} , an architect and entrepreneur († [[:en:1945|1945]] ). * [[:en:Keiō|Keiō]] 3rd year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1867|1867]] [[:en:October 25|October 25]] ） – [[:en:Hiranuma Kiichirō|Hiranuma Kiichirō]] , who later served as Prime Minister for the 35th time († [[:en:1952|1952]] ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Meiō|Meiō]] 9th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1500|1500]] [[:en:October 21|October 21]] ） – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Go-Tsuchimikado|Gotomonomine]] , the 103rd emperor (* [[:en:1442|1442]] ).
